title.narrative: Dignity and Rights in Central Asia

description.narrative: Objectives for Asia (South & Central Asia): The project has three main objectives. This first is to increase public knowledge and support of human rights. The second is to equip the government and various non-governmental organizations (NGOs) to support survivors of human trafficking. The last one is to improve or update human rights laws with a focus on safe migration and human trafficking.

Through the regional Dignity and Rights program, USAID will support activities with the Government of the Kyrgyz Republic and civil society partners that address Trafficking in Persons issues (across the spectrum of prevention, protection and policy reform) as well as activities in the trafficking in persons "nexus", such as migrants' rights and gender-based violence. Potential interventions include informational events, educational campaigns, and related media products supported by local civil society partners; protection services to support the return, rehabilitation, and reintegration of Victims of Trafficking (VOTs); improved general citizen awareness of rights-related issues, including trafficking; and improved mechanisms for cooperation between the Government of the Kyrgyz Republic, local society, and other regional actors.
